###############################################################################
###########################		CLS-CSI demo	###############################
###############################################################################

This is demo application of CLS-CSI. It will demonstrate:
CLS-CSI reporter on RDK:
	1) listen CLS-CSI report event from driver, by listening vendor NL80211 event.
	2) parse CSI data (info and I/Q data).
	3) send CSI data to CSI parser via socket.

CLS-CSI parser on server, in Python3:
	1) receive CSI data from CSI reporter.
	2) parse, print and store CSI data (in .csv) in server.

                  ---------------------------------
                  |         CLS-CSI parser         | @ PC/Server
                  |    (demo_clscsi_parser.py)     |
                  ---------------------------------
                                 ||
                                 ||
                               socket
                                 ||
                                 ||
                  ---------------------------------
                  |       CLS-CSI reporter         | @ RDK
                  |    (demo_clscsi_reporterd)     |
                  |               |                |
                  |               |                |
                  |           NL80211              |
                  |               |                |
                  |               |                |
                  |      CLS Wi-Fi driver/FW       |
                  ---------------------------------


###########################	Compile and install	###############################
This demo applications are disabled by default.

Steps to enable the CLS-CSI reporter:
On build server for SDK:
1) Modify [openwrt_dir]/cls-prods-config/cs8862a-rdk.config to add
   CONFIG_PACKAGE_clscsi-sample=y
2) $ cp [openwrt_dir]/cls-prods-config/cs8862a-rdk.config [openwrt_dir]/.config
3) $ make defconfig
4) $ make

On RDK
1) Load the new image, executable binary 'demo_clscsi_reporterd' is expected
   installed to /bin/ of rootfs in RDK.

Steps to install the CLS-CSI parser on PC/Server:
1) Copy ./src/demo_clscsi_parser.py to PC/Server.
2) Intsall Python3 on PC/Server.


###########################		Demo and Usage	###############################
On RDK:
	a) launch demo_clscsi_reporterd
	   $ demo_clscsi_reporterd -s <server_ip> &

	b) Enable CLS-CSI
	   $ clsapi enable csi <phyname> 1

	c) Associate a STA, and add it to CLS-CSI monitor list
	   $ clsapi add csi_sta <phyname> <STA MAC in aa:bb:cc:dd:ee:ff>

On PC/Server:
	a) launch CLS-CSI parser.
	   $ python3 demo_clscsi_parser.py

	b) CSI info will be printed on terminal, info and I/Q data will be saved to
	   './clscsi_data.csv'

